Information about these directories:

 - htdocs/
   is where you put the files you are publishing on your website. The first
   file presented to the visitors (eg: when they hit "http://<%= name %>/")
   must be named "index.html". "index.php" also works for PHP websites.

 - cgi-bin/
   is where you put scripts that will be executed when the get called. This
   directory gets available under the following URL:
   http://<%= name %>/cgi-bin/

 - private/
   you can put there anything that must be accessible by the web server but not
   published on the internet. For example password files or user sessions.

 - logs/
   you will find here the full access and error logs for your website.

 - conf/
   you can put apache configuration files in this directory. They will be
   integrated within the <VirtualHost> section of your website. For more
   details see http://httpd.apache.org/docs/

 - ssl/
   here are found the SSL certificates of your website, if you have https
   enabled.

